comment: You need to be careful when using this app: It makes no attempt to control the amount of space it takes, so if you don't (1) change the picture size to a small resolution, and (2) chose the option to only sync existing contacts rather than all Facebook contacts (the defaults are maximum picture size and all fb contacts), it might eat up A LOT of your internal memory if you have a lot of Facebook contacts. I have 1000+ contacts in my Google account, and they still only took about 8MB of internal space. When I installed this app, contact storage bloated to over 40MB (!!!) and filled my internal memory until I only had 14KB free, at which point the system naturally became unstable. I had to restart it several times and remove several smaller apps until I could have enough stability to delete this one. I also couldn't manage to merge the app's contacts with my Google contacts. This probably is not what the app is set to do, but it was what I was looking for, and unfortunately couldn't do it.
